mber_agreed_on_going_public_at":"2019-10-13T09:43:01.399Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"I. Summary\nAdobe Flash Player is prone to a vulnerability which leads to Use-After-Free. \n------------------------------------------------------------------\nII. Description\nIf the ASnative(900,1) is invoked with MovieClip instance and getter properties associated with swfRoot where the getter method includes a call to removeMovieClip(), the MovieClip instance is used after it is freed.\n\nLatest version of Adobe Flash Player 20.0.0.267 has been tested under Windows 7.\n------------------------------------------------------------------\nIII. Impact\nUse-After-Free\n------------------------------------------------------------------\nIV. Credit\nWen Guanxing from Venustech ADLAB is credited for this vulnerability.\n\nIt has been assigned by Adobe as CVE-2016-0982\nhttps://helpx.adobe.com/security/products/flash-player/apsb16-04.html","bounty_amount":"2000.0","formatted_bounty":"$2,000","weakness":{"id":2,"name":"Memory Corruption - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":76003,"file_name":"crash.swf","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/076/003/e146972cdc3a4b0e560ea3c4a2b6dddf519b9c9c/crash.swf?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22crash.swf%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27crash.swf\u0026response-content-type=application%2Foctet-stream\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQXG6W2HKE%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T091602Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECgaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJHMEUCIQCMt7Tu2%2Burv4UECBzNMPag02b0Nxq%2BIoP8Vpd5ZSYg%2FQIgCduj86AWWqau%2Bq%2B9KYVhNGBc7G7bCF%2Bp98ytqVgAU7cqugUI8f%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FARADGgwwMTM2MTkyNzQ4NDkiDFUSqHIOkXI%2FdY1eJCqOBZgwisrU2DzGzvl%2FhIFJTia